# Scratch & Demo Files

Don't scatter random files in the repo. Non-deliverable files have dedicated,
gitignored homes:

## `.scratch/` — throwaway
When a request is outside the main project's scope, experimental, or clearly
throwaway (one-off scripts, scratch notes, temp output, explorations), create
those files under `.scratch/` at the repo root.

- `.scratch/` is gitignored, so nothing in it is accidentally committed.
- Use it whenever we "go out of context" from the actual Allocato deliverable.
- If unsure whether something is throwaway, default to `.scratch/` and mention it.

## `demo/` — kept demos / manual run scripts
Demo and manual test-run scripts (e.g. console demos for trying the engine) go
in `demo/` at the repo root.

- `demo/` is gitignored - demos are kept local, not committed.
- Run via `npm run demo`.

## Always
- NEVER put genuine project deliverables in `.scratch/` or `demo/` - real source
  code, docs, and config go in their proper place in the repo.
- Unit tests stay as colocated `*.spec.ts` next to the code they test, NOT in
  `demo/` or `.scratch/`.
